mutant: m035_account_replay_guard_inverted
target: internal/ingest/live/consumer.go
failure-mode: |
  The #account replay guard's kind check is inverted (!= becomes ==), so
  the guard never examines an #account event — the exact pre-#231 state.
  A relay seq regression (relay restored from backup) re-delivers an
  account-delete which re-archives at a fresh jetstream seq ABOVE a later
  reactivate + recreate; every fold (oracle reconstruct, the tombstone
  set, compaction) then treats the account as deleted after the recreate
  and permanently erases live records from folded state and, after
  compaction, from the archive.
expected-detection: |
  replay tier: TestOracle_RelaySeqDuplicates / TestOracle_RelaySeqRegression
  drive the real live consumer against the simulator relay with a
  seq-replay fault over an account-delete/reactivate/recreate window and
  assert final-state convergence + exact-multiset event log + the guard's
  drop counter (anti-vacuity). With the guard vacuously disabled the
  replayed account-delete re-archives above the recreate: the drop-counter
  anti-vacuity assert fails first, and final-state Compare reports the
  recreated record missing. The live-package unit test
  TestProcessBatch_ReplayedAccountEventIsDroppedNotReArchived also fails.
expected-tier: replay
tiers: replay

